00:16:12.962 --> 00:16:15.122
- Why not?
- They got shot.

269
00:16:19.267 --> 00:16:22.896
- Don't open it. I don't want to know.
- Just relax.

270
00:16:23.271 --> 00:16:26.365
They're just my little furry friends.
Say. "Hi. Nelson."

271
00:16:26.608 --> 00:16:30.976
Somebody was gonna do nasty little
experiments on your brains.

272
00:16:31.178 --> 00:16:33.408
But I wouldn't have it.

273
00:16:38.385 --> 00:16:40.216
What do you do. by the way?

274
00:16:41.555 --> 00:16:43.420
I'm in advertising.

275
00:16:43.624 --> 00:16:45.319
Advertising.

276
00:16:46.060 --> 00:16:47.686
So you enjoy it?

277
00:16:48.661 --> 00:16:51.562
People tend to enjoy
what they're really good at.

278
00:16:54.400 --> 00:16:57.096
Besides your job.
what else makes you miserable?

279
00:16:58.338 --> 00:17:00.135
I mean. what do you do for fun?

280
00:17:03.176 --> 00:17:04.574
I didn't think so.

281
00:17:04.843 --> 00:17:06.970
No hobbies?

282
00:17:07.179 --> 00:17:09.909
No diversions? No kinky obsessions?

283
00:17:10.549 --> 00:17:13.211
For one quick second there.
I thought you--

284
00:17:13.418 --> 00:17:15.215
Just get in the car.

285
00:17:25.796 --> 00:17:27.661
Want to come up for cocoa?

286
00:17:29.000 --> 00:17:31.867
As titillating as the evening's been.
I'm afraid not.

287
00:17:34.038 --> 00:17:35.335
Okay.

288
00:17:37.173 --> 00:17:38.800
How about I make you a deal?

289
00:17:39.009 --> 00:17:42.706
Come up for one cup. and I'll
never ask you for another ride.

290
00:17:42.912 --> 00:17:44.470
No. thanks.

291
00:17:46.349 --> 00:17:47.338
Okay.

292
00:17:48.084 --> 00:17:49.278
Thanks.

293
00:17:51.121 --> 00:17:52.850
I'll see you tomorrow then.

294
00:17:53.056 --> 00:17:55.216
Whoa. whoa. whoa!

295
00:17:55.424 --> 00:17:56.618
Hold on.

296
00:17:56.825 --> 00:17:57.951
Hold on.

297
00:17:58.160 --> 00:17:59.889
8:00 is good for you. right?

298
00:18:00.095 --> 00:18:02.962
You. me. Manny. the doorman.
that whole thing?

299
00:18:20.648 --> 00:18:21.842
Come in.

300
00:18:27.654 --> 00:18:29.747
There you guys go.

301
00:18:41.735 --> 00:18:43.430
I can help you.

302
00:18:43.936 --> 00:18:45.665
See. I have a gift.

303
00:18:45.871 --> 00:18:48.533
A special ability
to help men with problems.

304
00:18:48.774 --> 00:18:50.071
I don't have problems.

305
00:18:51.177 --> 00:18:53.611
Now. see that. usually.
is the first sign.

306
00:18:53.813 --> 00:18:54.802
Of what?

307
00:18:55.014 --> 00:18:56.003
Denial.

308
00:18:56.215 --> 00:18:57.204
Denial?

309
00:18:57.450 --> 00:19:00.078
First of all.
I think you work too much.

310
00:19:00.286 --> 00:19:03.049
Really?
And what do you know about work?

311
00:19:03.855 --> 00:19:04.913
Plenty.

312
00:19:05.123 --> 00:19:08.991
You admitted you do nothing else
and it doesn't make you happy.

313
00:19:09.394 --> 00:19:11.555
I admitted nothing. I was silent.

314
00:19:11.763 --> 00:19:13.594
No special interests. no pets.

315
00:19:13.798 --> 00:19:14.787
You hate dogs.

316
00:19:14.999 --> 00:19:15.988
Busted.

317
00:19:16.201 --> 00:19:18.259
Actually I do have a pet. a fish.

318
00:19:18.602 --> 00:19:19.864
A fish?

319
00:19:20.070 --> 00:19:22.129
Doesn't count. Cold-blooded. Sorry.

320
00:19:22.940 --> 00:19:26.103
No. you are a walking case study.

321
00:19:27.311 --> 00:19:28.300
Look at you.

322
00:19:29.046 --> 00:19:31.674
You're a workaholic
at such an advanced stage...

323
00:19:31.882 --> 00:19:35.339
...that your intimacy skills have
withered away to almost nothing.

324
00:19:35.551 --> 00:19:36.609
Left untreated...

325
00:19:36.819 --> 00:19:39.287
...you could become
emotionally extinct.

326
00:19:40.389 --> 00:19:42.186
Out of sheer perverse curiosity...

327
00:19:42.391 --> 00:19:45.622
...how does a lunatic like you
help a guy like me?

328
00:19:48.097 --> 00:19:49.928
You live in a box.

329
00:19:51.099 --> 00:19:52.498
I could lift the lid...

330
00:19:52.701 --> 00:19:53.895
...let some light in.

331
00:19:55.170 --> 00:19:57.263
Wow. that's deep.

332
00:19:58.140 --> 00:20:00.472
I feel almost cured just hearing it.

333
00:20:02.444 --> 00:20:03.706
Well...

334
00:20:03.912 --> 00:20:05.243
...if you want my help...

335
00:20:05.447 --> 00:20:07.710
...it'll require a commitment
on your part.

336
00:20:09.917 --> 00:20:12.613
You have to live with me here
for a month.

337
00:20:14.155 --> 00:20:15.554
No more. no less...

338
00:20:15.756 --> 00:20:17.018
...and no work allowed.

339
00:20:19.894 --> 00:20:21.361
You don't even know me...

340
00:20:21.729 --> 00:20:24.196
...and you're inviting me to move in?

341
00:20:25.532 --> 00:20:29.332
And how's my girlfriend
supposed to feel about that?

342
00:20:30.203 --> 00:20:31.397
Girlfriend?

343
00:20:31.604 --> 00:20:33.595
You don't have a girlfriend.

344
00:20:35.074 --> 00:20:37.338
I mean. it's something you feel.

345
00:20:37.744 --> 00:20:41.577
There's something intimate a woman
leaves on a man that you don't have.

346
00:20:42.114 --> 00:20:43.513
Her name's Angelica.

347
00:20:46.919 --> 00:20:48.887
Well. I feel sorry for Angelica.

348
00:20:49.388 --> 00:20:50.548
Great.

349
00:20:52.090 --> 00:20:56.322
I'll relay that to her when I leave.
Which is... right about now.

350
00:20:56.795 --> 00:20:58.853
October's almost over.

351
00:20:59.230 --> 00:21:01.460
We can start midnight...

352
00:21:01.666 --> 00:21:03.395
...first of November.

353
00:21:03.601 --> 00:21:07.560
If you're brave enough to commit.
I'll devote myself entirely to you.

354
00:21:09.073 --> 00:21:12.099
Brave enough. but not stupid enough.

355
00:21:12.410 --> 00:21:14.468
Now listen up. moonbeam.

356
00:21:14.678 --> 00:21:15.872
Here's how it works.

357
00:21:16.479 --> 00:21:18.504
No more harassment. No more rides.

358
00:21:18.715 --> 00:21:20.114
No more extortion.

359
00:21:20.450 --> 00:21:22.509
Next time you come into my building...

360
00:21:22.953 --> 00:21:24.944
...I really will call the cops.

361
00:21:39.335 --> 00:21:41.269
This is your image. Mr. Leach.

362
00:21:41.804 --> 00:21:43.738
We polled your primary demographic.

363
00:21:44.039 --> 00:21:45.904
I Know what 89 percent said?

364
00:21:46.242 --> 00:21:47.469
"Boring."

365
00:21:47.842 --> 00:21:49.309
"Safe."

366
00:21:52.714 --> 00:21:54.705
We need to drop a bomb.

367
00:21:54.949 --> 00:21:57.884
You don't want hot dogs "safe."

368
00:21:58.286 --> 00:21:59.651
What's in a hot dog?

369
00:21:59.854 --> 00:22:02.118
Don't tell me. I don't want to know.

370
00:22:04.324 --> 00:22:05.791
They're dangerous.

371
00:22:06.593 --> 00:22:08.060
What are we selling here?

372
00:22:08.262 --> 00:22:11.231
We're selling temptation. desire...

373
00:22:11.431 --> 00:22:12.898
...animal instincts...

374
00:22:13.300 --> 00:22:14.995
...gluttony. sin.

375
00:22:15.602 --> 00:22:18.196
We want to show man as he really is.

376
00:22:18.405 --> 00:22:19.463
A savage.

377
00:22:20.073 --> 00:22:21.835
He needs fire. He needs food.

378
00:22:22.108 --> 00:22:23.405
He hunts and gathers.

379
00:22:23.609 --> 00:22:24.974
What does he get?

380
00:22:26.412 --> 00:22:27.743
He gets a hot dog.

381
00:22:28.114 --> 00:22:29.240
We're pagans.

382
00:22:29.448 --> 00:22:30.642
We love our rituals.

383
00:22:30.850 --> 00:22:33.410
Our team hits a home run.
we're screaming.

384
00:22:33.619 --> 00:22:35.052
What do we want?

385
00:22:36.055 --> 00:22:37.215
We want a hot dog.

386
00:22:37.422 --> 00:22:39.856
Let's go to your
preteen demographic.

387
00:22:40.225 --> 00:22:41.954
Kids. the little angels.

388
00:22:42.160 --> 00:22:44.094
They're not. They're monsters.

389
00:22:44.296 --> 00:22:47.732
We give them a tuna sandwich.
they don't want a tuna sandwich.

390
00:22:47.933 --> 00:22:50.333
They want a hot dog!

391
00:22:51.136 --> 00:22:52.296
We need women.

392
00:22:52.504 --> 00:22:53.698
We've got the mothers...

393
00:22:54.538 --> 00:22:55.869
...we want their daughters.

394
00:22:56.240 --> 00:22:59.004
Let's ask that age-old question:

395
00:22:59.209 --> 00:23:01.905
"What does a woman really want?"

396
00:23:02.246 --> 00:23:03.235
You know.

397
00:23:03.447 --> 00:23:04.607
I know.

398
00:23:05.816 --> 00:23:07.306
She wants a hot dog.

399
00:23:07.718 --> 00:23:09.686
We're hot-blooded. We need sex!

400
00:23:09.887 --> 00:23:12.514
We need a sinful. dangerous food!

401
00:23:12.722 --> 00:23:14.189
What is it?

402
00:23:15.158 --> 00:23:17.183
It's a hot dog!

403
00:23:17.627 --> 00:23:19.595
It's a hot dog!

404
00:23:19.796 --> 00:23:22.060
It's a hot dog!

405
00:23:23.266 --> 00:23:24.358
It's a hot dog.

406
00:23:24.567 --> 00:23:27.831
"Dr. Diggity. It's a hot dog."

407
00:23:38.547 --> 00:23:39.536
No.

408
00:23:43.719 --> 00:23:44.844
No?

409
00:23:45.953 --> 00:23:47.011
What do you mean?

410
00:23:47.488 --> 00:23:49.149
It's not for us.

411
00:23:49.357 --> 00:23:52.053
You don't understand our company.

412
00:23:52.259 --> 00:23:54.124
I don't understand?

413
00:23:57.431 --> 00:23:59.228
What did you ask us for?

414
00:23:59.600 --> 00:24:00.692
Edge.

415
00:24:00.934 --> 00:24:03.061
This is edge.

416
00:24:03.403 --> 00:24:05.837
We're going with Baker Bohanon.

417
00:24:06.039 --> 00:24:08.098
I think you're making a mistake.

418
00:24:09.075 --> 00:24:11.669
I've seen your sales.
You're in big trouble.

419
00:24:12.045 --> 00:24:15.845
Oh. no. We are America's
favorite hot dog. son.

420
00:24:16.116 --> 00:24:17.946
Were. Were.

421
00:24:18.283 --> 00:24:19.443
You're a dinosaur.

422
00:24:19.918 --> 00:24:21.943
You're flat-lining.

423
00:24:23.088 --> 00:24:24.487
You're dead meat.

424
00:24:24.690 --> 00:24:27.158
And you just went too far.
you little punk.

425
00:24:27.359 --> 00:24:30.157
So I'll tell you
what I really think of your campaign.

426
00:24:30.362 --> 00:24:32.626
This is cheap. tasteless crap.

427
00:24:32.831 --> 00:24:33.820
Really?

428
00:24:34.033 --> 00:24:36.227
That's funny.
because so is your product.

429
00:24:36.434 --> 00:24:37.264
Stop it.

430
00:24:37.468 --> 00:24:39.766
I make a wholesome hot dog. you prick.

431
00:24:39.971 --> 00:24:41.233
It's mystery meat.

432
00:24:41.439 --> 00:24:44.499
- Come on. Nelson!
- It's toxic waste in a tube!

433
00:24:45.009 --> 00:24:46.476
You're killing me!

434
00:24:46.677 --> 00:24:49.202
You're killing us!
You're killing all of us!

435
00:24:49.414 --> 00:24:50.880
Mr. Leach! Hey. buddy!

436
00:24:56.486 --> 00:24:59.011
What the hell happened in there?

437
00:24:59.222 --> 00:25:00.246
I know.

438
00:25:00.457 --> 00:25:01.947
Can you believe that asshole?

439
00:25:02.159 --> 00:25:04.127
Baker Bohanon.

440
00:25:06.897 --> 00:25:09.524
I've always said you're brilliant.
A machine.

441
00:25:09.732 --> 00:25:12.792
But I knew one day you'd snap.
and we'd all burn.

442
00:25:13.335 --> 00:25:15.269
What are you talking about. burn?

443
00:25:15.471 --> 00:25:18.736
You know what was at stake?
How many millions you lost?

444
00:25:19.275 --> 00:25:22.369
You just dragged my agency's name
through the gutter.

445
00:25:22.578 --> 00:25:23.875
Hold on a second.

446
00:25:24.080 --> 00:25:25.171
Gutter?

447
00:25:25.380 --> 00:25:27.371
I'm the best thing this agency's got.

448
00:25:27.882 --> 00:25:30.783
And that rabid dog routine
makes you the best?

449
00:25:30.985 --> 00:25:33.010
I don't think so.
It makes you a wreck!

450
00:25:33.221 --> 00:25:35.485
It makes you a liability.

451
00:25:36.458 --> 00:25:38.358
You need a vacation. Now.

452
00:25:38.560 --> 00:25:39.993
Screw vacation.

453
00:25:40.195 --> 00:25:42.526
Give me another account. Come on.

454
00:25:42.996 --> 00:25:45.294
Nelson. did you hear me?

455
00:25:45.499 --> 00:25:46.761
Take a vacation.

456
00:25:47.367 --> 00:25:49.892
Short or permanent. your choice.

457
00:25:51.271 --> 00:25:52.738
Are you threatening me?

458
00:25:55.742 --> 00:25:57.403
That's hilarious.

459
00:25:57.610 --> 00:26:00.204
I'm two Clio's ahead of the game. Ray.

460
00:26:00.413 --> 00:26:02.608
You can't afford to lose me.

461
00:26:03.149 --> 00:26:04.275
You're fired.

462
00:26:05.885 --> 00:26:06.874
Say that again.

463
00:26:09.388 --> 00:26:11.219
I don't think I heard you.

464
00:26:11.324 --> 00:26:12.757
You're fired!

465
00:26:34.044 --> 00:26:35.341
God. am I...

466
00:26:35.546 --> 00:26:36.843
...glad to see you.

467
00:26:40.684 --> 00:26:43.016
You've got to be kidding me.

468
00:27:07.209 --> 00:27:08.699
Mr. Moss?

469
00:27:09.244 --> 00:27:10.939
Are you doing okay?

470
00:27:11.580 --> 00:27:12.569
I'm fine.

471
00:27:12.981 --> 00:27:14.608
You have a deliv--

472
00:27:16.251 --> 00:27:18.219
You have delivery.

473
00:27:19.922 --> 00:27:23.357
- Leave it!
- I do not think you want me do that.

474
00:27:23.658 --> 00:27:26.252
It's from the crazy lady
from the other night.

475
00:27:26.460 --> 00:27:28.724
She tell me I have to deliver
in the flesh.

476
00:27:28.930 --> 00:27:30.261
I said. leave it!

477
00:27:30.831 --> 00:27:32.196
Okay.

478
00:27:56.589 --> 00:27:59.023
You've got to be kidding me.

479
00:28:08.067 --> 00:28:09.125
Hey!

480
00:28:09.535 --> 00:28:12.469
Do me a favor. Stay out of my life.

481
00:28:12.670 --> 00:28:13.796
Goodbye.

482
00:28:14.005 --> 00:28:15.165
Is that Ernie?

483
00:28:15.373 --> 00:28:16.806
It's Ernie!

484
00:28:17.008 --> 00:28:19.306
I missed you so much! Hi.

485
00:28:19.510 --> 00:28:21.034
Did you rethink my offer?

486
00:28:21.246 --> 00:28:24.306
I don't feel like playing
the Deever Mad Hatter game.

487
00:28:24.515 --> 00:28:25.709
What is this?

488
00:28:25.917 --> 00:28:27.781
- What happened?
- Nothing.

489
00:28:27.985 --> 00:28:30.545
- Can I look at it?
- Why?

490
00:28:31.121 --> 00:28:33.089
Because I'm a vampire.

491
00:28:35.392 --> 00:28:36.723
Because it's bleeding.

492
00:28:37.060 --> 00:28:40.826
And maybe....
Maybe I can help you.

493
00:28:42.432 --> 00:28:44.831
What are you after?
What do you want from me?

494
00:28:47.370 --> 00:28:48.803
You should come with me.

495
00:28:50.172 --> 00:28:52.470
Why are you sending me dogs?

496
00:28:57.313 --> 00:29:00.043
So. what did you do today?

497
00:29:00.416 --> 00:29:02.212
What did I do today?

498
00:29:04.119 --> 00:29:05.711
I got fired.

499
00:29:06.221 --> 00:29:08.189
They took the company car...

500
00:29:08.890 --> 00:29:10.858
...and my girlfriend left me.

501
00:29:12.160 --> 00:29:13.149
Perfect.

502
00:29:14.729 --> 00:29:15.991
Define "perfect."

503
00:29:16.364 --> 00:29:17.661
Well...

504
00:29:18.532 --> 00:29:20.227
...it's the first of November.

505
00:29:20.434 --> 00:29:22.368
Our month to be together.

506
00:29:22.870 --> 00:29:25.100
You're actually serious about this.

507
00:29:25.306 --> 00:29:26.534
Oh. yeah. Very.

508
00:29:26.940 --> 00:29:29.875
You think I'm just gonna
drop everything?

509
00:29:31.912 --> 00:29:35.938
I don't want to bust your bubble.
but it sounds like you already have.

510
00:29:36.149 --> 00:29:37.810
Live here...

511
00:29:38.184 --> 00:29:40.914
...and let you mess with my head
for a whole month?

512
00:29:41.988 --> 00:29:44.456
I don't know if I would
put it that way...

513
00:29:44.657 --> 00:29:47.023
...but yeah. I think you should.

514
00:29:47.727 --> 00:29:49.854
I'm sorry. I can't stand watches.

515
00:29:51.863 --> 00:29:53.194
So this...

516
00:29:53.398 --> 00:29:54.888
...whatever you call it--

517
00:29:55.100 --> 00:29:57.534
- Help.
- "Help."

518
00:29:59.171 --> 00:30:00.604
What are you doing?

519
00:30:00.806 --> 00:30:02.205
Taking your shirt off.

520
00:30:02.407 --> 00:30:03.533
Why?

521
00:30:04.676 --> 00:30:06.507
So you can clean up.

522
00:30:07.945 --> 00:30:09.037
Why?

523
00:30:12.049 --> 00:30:14.574
Because you smell like puppy pee.

524
00:30:39.309 --> 00:30:40.970
Just for the night.

525
00:31:51.376 --> 00:31:52.843
Whoa. Hey.

526
00:31:53.044 --> 00:31:54.375
Okay.

527
00:31:54.846 --> 00:31:55.938
What?

528
00:31:58.082 --> 00:31:59.879
Slow. you know.

529
00:32:01.152 --> 00:32:02.176
Yeah.

530
00:32:04.721 --> 00:32:06.188
Gentle.

531
00:32:07.825 --> 00:32:09.315
Look at me.

532
00:32:25.908 --> 00:32:28.433
This is not very comfortable.

533
00:32:29.912 --> 00:32:32.210
Wait. what are you doing?

534
00:32:32.915 --> 00:32:34.712
What does it look like I'm doing?

535
00:32:34.917 --> 00:32:37.078
Wait. just go slow.

536
00:32:37.587 --> 00:32:38.712
Just--

537
00:32:39.321 --> 00:32:41.846
What's wrong? What's wrong?

538
00:32:43.158 --> 00:32:45.626
- Where are you going?
- To hell with this!

539
00:32:45.861 --> 00:32:47.328
But. wait--

540
00:32:52.067 --> 00:32:53.796
Please wait!

541
00:32:55.669 --> 00:32:57.899
Will you just wait a second?

