1294
01:27:34.117 --> 01:27:36.210
Sara. I stood on the street...

1295
01:27:37.354 --> 01:27:39.219
...and I realized...

1296
01:27:40.657 --> 01:27:42.021
...this is it.

1297
01:27:42.725 --> 01:27:44.522
Life will never be better...

1298
01:27:45.094 --> 01:27:47.028
...or sweeter than this.

1299
01:27:47.630 --> 01:27:49.029
I'm happy.

1300
01:27:50.032 --> 01:27:51.465
I'm in love.

1301
01:27:52.935 --> 01:27:54.266
Marry me.

1302
01:27:57.440 --> 01:27:59.532
That's incredibly sweet.

1303
01:28:02.310 --> 01:28:05.643
- But you don't understand.
- Yes. I do. It all makes sense.

1304
01:28:06.981 --> 01:28:08.539
I want you.

1305
01:28:08.817 --> 01:28:10.648
I want this life.

1306
01:28:21.028 --> 01:28:22.427
Marry me.

1307
01:28:27.801 --> 01:28:29.462
Marry me. Sara.

1308
01:28:34.974 --> 01:28:37.442
- I can't.
- Why not?

1309
01:28:39.245 --> 01:28:40.803
Because of me.

1310
01:28:41.147 --> 01:28:42.136
What about you?

1311
01:28:42.348 --> 01:28:44.612
For God's sake. Sara.
Please. just--

1312
01:28:44.817 --> 01:28:46.250
Just tell me what's wrong.

1313
01:28:46.652 --> 01:28:48.346
Tell me the truth.

1314
01:28:50.122 --> 01:28:51.384
I can't.

1315
01:28:54.226 --> 01:28:55.625
Sara?

1316
01:29:04.935 --> 01:29:05.924
Jesus.

1317
01:29:07.238 --> 01:29:08.227
I'm fine.

1318
01:29:09.240 --> 01:29:11.606
No. I'm fine.

1319
01:29:12.343 --> 01:29:14.504
- I'm fine.
- What the hell is going on?

1320
01:29:14.879 --> 01:29:16.506
No. Nelson.

1321
01:29:17.948 --> 01:29:20.644
No. Nelson. no!

1322
01:29:23.586 --> 01:29:24.678
No.

1323
01:29:29.192 --> 01:29:31.251
Is this what you wanted to see?

1324
01:29:31.928 --> 01:29:33.293
This is it!

1325
01:29:34.731 --> 01:29:37.097
Is this enough truth for you?

1326
01:29:37.300 --> 01:29:38.630
Does this make you happy?

1327
01:29:38.834 --> 01:29:42.793
Goddamn you!
You just couldn't leave it alone!

1328
01:29:43.438 --> 01:29:44.632
Sara. stop.

1329
01:29:44.840 --> 01:29:48.833
You just couldn't leave it--
God. just leave it alone.

1330
01:30:07.361 --> 01:30:09.829
It's non-Hodgkin's lymphoma.

1331
01:30:12.766 --> 01:30:14.097
It's a type of cancer.

1332
01:30:16.102 --> 01:30:19.128
You shouldn't have to find out
like this. I'm sorry.

1333
01:30:21.675 --> 01:30:23.734
She's gonna be asleep for hours.

1334
01:30:23.944 --> 01:30:26.936
You want to go for a walk.
have a chat or something?

1335
01:30:29.148 --> 01:30:31.412
- Yeah.
- Yeah. okay.

1336
01:30:39.491 --> 01:30:42.119
You said she stopped
her treatments a year ago?

1337
01:30:44.029 --> 01:30:45.859
What about the pills?

1338
01:30:46.164 --> 01:30:49.656
It just gets her through the day.
She stopped trying to beat it.

1339
01:30:49.867 --> 01:30:53.030
She did it all for a year.
Nothing worked.

1340
01:30:53.371 --> 01:30:57.535
Look. I'm no doctor. but when
you're unchecked. wouldn't that--?

1341
01:30:57.742 --> 01:30:58.731
Yeah.

1342
01:31:00.345 --> 01:31:01.902
It's spread everywhere.

1343
01:31:09.152 --> 01:31:12.644
How could she get involved with me
and not tell me she was sick?

1344
01:31:15.392 --> 01:31:17.189
I mean. what was she thinking?

1345
01:31:17.661 --> 01:31:21.596
She was thinking you'd
be the same as all the others.

1346
01:31:21.897 --> 01:31:23.888
She'd dump you after a month.

1347
01:31:25.568 --> 01:31:28.002
You've got to understand something.

1348
01:31:28.571 --> 01:31:30.471
She's completely powerless.

1349
01:31:30.673 --> 01:31:33.233
With these rules. you know...

1350
01:31:33.442 --> 01:31:37.673
...they give her the illusion
and dignity of control.

1351
01:31:38.413 --> 01:31:40.108
It's kept her alive.

1352
01:31:42.651 --> 01:31:45.415
The rift with her family.
that's what it's about?

1353
01:31:45.620 --> 01:31:46.814
These rules.

1354
01:31:48.556 --> 01:31:49.580
Yeah.

1355
01:31:50.759 --> 01:31:53.750
Her family couldn't handle it.
They wouldn't let go.

1356
01:31:53.961 --> 01:31:56.259
They kept trying to run her disease.

1357
01:31:56.463 --> 01:31:57.896
So she took off.

1358
01:31:58.098 --> 01:31:59.656
And came here?

1359
01:32:02.670 --> 01:32:05.434
She told me if she couldn't
live a normal life...

1360
01:32:05.639 --> 01:32:09.734
...she was determined to live an
abnormal one the best way she could.

1361
01:32:12.045 --> 01:32:13.478
I don't get it.

1362
01:32:17.050 --> 01:32:20.577
She loves life more
than anyone I've ever met.

1363
01:32:21.154 --> 01:32:22.951
How can she just give up?

1364
01:32:23.156 --> 01:32:25.589
You listening to anything
I'm telling you?

1365
01:32:25.791 --> 01:32:27.156
She's not giving up.

1366
01:32:27.359 --> 01:32:30.760
She's making the most
of the time she's got left.

1367
01:32:31.930 --> 01:32:33.420
Don't mess with that.

1368
01:32:39.504 --> 01:32:41.028
I'm sorry.

1369
01:32:44.275 --> 01:32:46.743
I didn't want you to see any of this.

1370
01:32:49.480 --> 01:32:51.175
I wanted you...

1371
01:32:51.515 --> 01:32:55.007
...to know me loving life. you know?

1372
01:32:56.420 --> 01:32:57.717
Come here.

1373
01:33:15.138 --> 01:33:17.230
Will you do something for me?

1374
01:33:18.807 --> 01:33:19.899
Anything.

1375
01:33:20.943 --> 01:33:22.740
Will you get me out of here?

1376
01:33:23.979 --> 01:33:25.105
Take me home.

1377
01:33:42.463 --> 01:33:43.691
Okay.

1378
01:34:05.351 --> 01:34:06.613
Jesus.

1379
01:34:14.293 --> 01:34:15.453
They're here.

1380
01:34:16.595 --> 01:34:17.926
Hey. darling.

1381
01:34:18.164 --> 01:34:19.153
Hey. sweetie.

1382
01:34:19.365 --> 01:34:21.162
You're sick? You look fabulous.

1383
01:34:21.367 --> 01:34:23.197
Oh. this is just a lie.

1384
01:34:23.401 --> 01:34:24.766
You look great.

1385
01:34:24.969 --> 01:34:28.200
- Want a nice. warm bath?
- Come on. sweetie.

1386
01:34:28.406 --> 01:34:30.806
- We'll run you a bath.
- What's on the menu tonight?

1387
01:34:31.009 --> 01:34:34.536
- We have lovely appetizers.
- Nice codeine.

1388
01:34:34.746 --> 01:34:38.772
Codeine? What else?
Donnatal. that's your favorite.

1389
01:34:38.982 --> 01:34:41.678
Come on. girl. Let's get you in here.

1390
01:34:41.885 --> 01:34:43.045
Okay.

1391
01:34:44.988 --> 01:34:45.977
Nice and easy.

1392
01:34:46.457 --> 01:34:49.984
Sara. I know doctors I could call.

1393
01:34:50.961 --> 01:34:52.223
No doctors.

1394
01:34:53.263 --> 01:34:57.824
I'm gonna be fine. Nelson.
But you can't be here.

1395
01:34:59.101 --> 01:35:01.797
I don't want you here.
You can't see this.

1396
01:35:02.104 --> 01:35:04.368
Please. go.

1397
01:35:04.574 --> 01:35:06.098
Okay. okay. he's going.

1398
01:35:07.610 --> 01:35:10.272
I can't stand by and do nothing.
just watch her....

1399
01:35:10.713 --> 01:35:11.702
Die?

1400
01:35:12.981 --> 01:35:14.915
That's why she wants you to go.

1401
01:35:15.417 --> 01:35:16.406
Go on.

1402
01:35:29.864 --> 01:35:31.161
Hey. Abner.

1403
01:35:33.267 --> 01:35:35.235
Today's not gonna be a great play day.

1404
01:35:35.870 --> 01:35:38.634
I know.
It's gonna be Father Sunday.

1405
01:35:38.839 --> 01:35:40.170
Did you forget?

1406
01:35:42.710 --> 01:35:44.610
Oh. God. I'm sorry. Ab. I can't.

1407
01:35:47.413 --> 01:35:49.210
But you promised.

1408
01:35:50.550 --> 01:35:52.108
I guess I don't have a dad.

1409
01:35:52.318 --> 01:35:55.549
I mean. I do.
but I don't know who he is.

1410
01:35:56.356 --> 01:35:57.755
So I brought Nelson.

1411
01:35:58.892 --> 01:36:02.156
We do stuff. and it's fun.
because he makes me feel smart.

1412
01:36:03.729 --> 01:36:05.663
I guess I feel like...

1413
01:36:06.098 --> 01:36:09.261
...if I got into trouble.
he'd take care of me.

1414
01:36:09.835 --> 01:36:13.202
Kind of like a best friend.
just bigger.

1415
01:36:15.073 --> 01:36:16.631
Thank you. Abner.

1416
01:36:20.344 --> 01:36:22.403
I guess I'll see you tomorrow.

1417
01:36:23.314 --> 01:36:26.147
I don't know.
I probably won't be here tomorrow.

1418
01:36:26.350 --> 01:36:27.544
How come?

1419
01:36:27.885 --> 01:36:30.581
I gotta do some thinking.
make a tough decision.

1420
01:36:33.891 --> 01:36:37.826
Sara thinks you don't respect her
choices? Something like that?

1421
01:36:38.795 --> 01:36:41.127
I don't know.
You always see that stuff on TV.

1422
01:36:42.232 --> 01:36:44.723
I think you're the coolest kid
I've ever met.

1423
01:36:44.935 --> 01:36:47.233
- I'll see you.
- See you.

1424
01:36:47.904 --> 01:36:49.371
Take care.

1425
01:38:26.296 --> 01:38:27.558
Shit.

1426
01:38:27.765 --> 01:38:28.925
You all right?

1427
01:38:29.967 --> 01:38:32.457
- Yeah. Yeah. I'm fine.
- Good.

1428
01:38:35.505 --> 01:38:39.874
I was planning on serving the pumpkin
on the floor. so this is....

1429
01:38:40.076 --> 01:38:41.270
This is really good.

1430
01:38:42.645 --> 01:38:44.510
Oh. God. Chaz.

1431
01:38:44.914 --> 01:38:47.041
Please tell me we're gonna have fun.

1432
01:38:48.884 --> 01:38:51.375
Thanksgiving's fun. right?
It's fun.

1433
01:38:51.820 --> 01:38:53.447
It'll be a riot.

1434
01:38:54.990 --> 01:38:56.389
Come here.

1435
01:38:56.825 --> 01:38:58.190
Give us a cuddle.

1436
01:39:02.164 --> 01:39:03.722
I need some fun.

1437
01:39:06.667 --> 01:39:08.828
You know. he asked me to marry him.

1438
01:39:09.704 --> 01:39:11.365
He's not the first.

1439
01:39:15.609 --> 01:39:18.874
No. but it was the first time
I wanted to say yes.

1440
01:39:19.647 --> 01:39:21.080
So why didn't you?

1441
01:39:23.850 --> 01:39:27.251
Because. Chaz. I let the whole thing
go too far.

1442
01:39:27.454 --> 01:39:29.888
Oh. yeah? Too far for who?

1443
01:39:30.824 --> 01:39:32.348
Both of us.

1444
01:39:33.593 --> 01:39:34.582
Anyway....

1445
01:39:35.662 --> 01:39:38.187
No need to talk about it.
He's gone.

1446
01:39:38.665 --> 01:39:42.600
Well. you did kick him out.
He'll be back if you let him.

1447
01:39:46.238 --> 01:39:48.229
I don't want him to come back.

1448
01:39:49.007 --> 01:39:49.996
Right.

1449
01:39:51.977 --> 01:39:54.707
You know. it's okay to break
your own rules. Sara.

1450
01:39:55.547 --> 01:39:57.537
You fell in love.

1451
01:39:57.982 --> 01:39:59.381
That's great.

1452
01:39:59.650 --> 01:40:03.051
It may not follow your master plan.
but you can't control everything.

1453
01:40:03.254 --> 01:40:04.482
Okay. just stop it.

1454
01:40:04.856 --> 01:40:07.256
I really don't need this
right now. Chaz.

1455
01:40:08.526 --> 01:40:09.720
Jesus!

1456
01:40:10.862 --> 01:40:15.594
There's no rule that gives me the
right to put him through all of this.

1457
01:40:15.799 --> 01:40:17.061
This hell.

1458
01:40:17.300 --> 01:40:18.790
I don't....

1459
01:40:22.305 --> 01:40:25.900
- It'll just hurt him in the end.
- It'll hurt. whatever you do.

1460
01:40:26.576 --> 01:40:27.668
We all will.

1461
01:40:28.378 --> 01:40:29.366
But...

1462
01:40:30.746 --> 01:40:32.976
...if I've learned anything...

1463
01:40:33.182 --> 01:40:35.912
...it's that you should have
those who love you near...

1464
01:40:36.118 --> 01:40:38.484
...as long as you possibly can.

1465
01:40:44.794 --> 01:40:45.782
Yeah.

1466
01:40:47.095 --> 01:40:49.188
Toast! Toast.

1467
01:40:51.099 --> 01:40:53.363
Happy we-stole-your-land-
and-killed-your-people day.

1468
01:40:53.568 --> 01:40:55.866
- Oh. Al.
- That's a good one. Al.

1469
01:40:59.073 --> 01:41:00.540
Here's to you.

1470
01:41:00.742 --> 01:41:03.039
- Here you go. babe.
- Here's to you.

1471
01:41:06.413 --> 01:41:07.402
Merry Christmas!

1472
01:41:13.387 --> 01:41:15.514
Merry Christmas!

1473
01:41:20.026 --> 01:41:21.391
Merry Christmas. Sara.

1474
01:41:31.971 --> 01:41:34.030
I think it's Thanksgiving. isn't it?

1475
01:41:34.273 --> 01:41:35.570
Not for you.

1476
01:41:35.807 --> 01:41:37.468
You shouldn't have to wait.

1477
01:41:40.679 --> 01:41:44.513
Does anyone else have
a sudden desire for Chinese food?

1478
01:41:44.716 --> 01:41:46.684
- Right on!
- Yeah.

1479
01:41:47.152 --> 01:41:48.710
It's good to see you. Nelson.

1480
01:41:50.288 --> 01:41:55.281
Do you know how the Chinese
celebrate Christmas and Thanksgiving?

1481
01:41:56.360 --> 01:41:57.452
Ciao. Santa.

1482
01:41:57.661 --> 01:41:59.128
I thought you'd never get here.

1483
01:41:59.330 --> 01:42:01.389
Come on. let's go.

1484
01:42:06.070 --> 01:42:09.436
For you. my sweet Sara...

1485
01:42:10.740 --> 01:42:14.836
...I bring you 12 gifts of Christmas.

1486
01:42:19.249 --> 01:42:20.273
One:

1487
01:42:24.020 --> 01:42:28.046
The famous Colombo log.
The salami that started it all.

1488
01:42:31.293 --> 01:42:32.282
Two:

1489
01:42:34.162 --> 01:42:39.122
A kaleidoscope of a coiffeur.
for the barking-mad pet crusader.

1490
01:42:41.670 --> 01:42:43.068
Number three:

1491
01:42:43.337 --> 01:42:46.170
A bullwhip for the dizzy dominatrix.

1492
01:42:46.374 --> 01:42:49.935
So you can rule your world in style
and whip me into shape.

1493
01:42:52.446 --> 01:42:53.435
Four:

1494
01:42:54.315 --> 01:42:55.407
I present...

1495
01:42:56.250 --> 01:42:59.048
...Sara. a custom-made fragrance
capturing...

1496
01:42:59.252 --> 01:43:01.652
...that special something...

1497
01:43:01.855 --> 01:43:04.653
...a woman leaves on a man.

1498
01:43:08.862 --> 01:43:11.660
- Nelson. this is....
- Only the beginning.

1499
01:43:11.965 --> 01:43:12.954
Five:

1500
01:43:15.468 --> 01:43:18.334
Why is Harriet so Hairy?

1501
01:43:18.537 --> 01:43:23.406
The definitive guide to understanding
our transvestite friends.

1502
01:43:25.611 --> 01:43:26.839
Six:

1503
01:43:27.046 --> 01:43:31.847
Tiny bubbles. for those leisurely
soaks we love so much.

1504
01:43:33.184 --> 01:43:34.173
Number seven:

1505
01:43:35.453 --> 01:43:37.978
A hundred muni train tokens...

1506
01:43:38.456 --> 01:43:40.424
...for the many. many...

1507
01:43:40.625 --> 01:43:42.855
...great rides of your life.

1508
01:43:45.463 --> 01:43:46.987
Number eight:

1509
01:43:48.366 --> 01:43:50.265
A collection of music to swoon by.

1510
01:43:50.667 --> 01:43:54.763
Which. by the way. happens to go
very nicely with gift number nine:

1511
01:43:55.939 --> 01:43:57.338
Dance classes.

1512
01:43:58.075 --> 01:44:02.205
Mildred's Academy of Dance.
guaranteed to get you off my toes...

1513
01:44:03.580 --> 01:44:04.842
...in a week.

1514
01:44:05.415 --> 01:44:08.042
- You sure?
- I'm positive.

1515
01:44:08.284 --> 01:44:09.842
Number 10:

1516
01:44:10.453 --> 01:44:14.150
For the gentle lady
who hates doing dishes.

1517
01:44:14.357 --> 01:44:15.551
A dishwasher!

1518
01:44:21.430 --> 01:44:23.192
Nelson. this is too much.

1519
01:44:23.865 --> 01:44:25.127
It's not enough.

1520
01:44:26.601 --> 01:44:27.625
Number 11:

1521
01:44:28.069 --> 01:44:32.301
Live. and in your apartment.
back by popular demand...

1522
01:44:32.507 --> 01:44:34.031
...I give you...

1523
01:44:35.043 --> 01:44:36.533
...Ernie!

1524
01:44:39.880 --> 01:44:41.438
Hi. baby!

1525
01:44:43.884 --> 01:44:45.476
I missed you.

1526
01:44:47.054 --> 01:44:52.082
And if this last gift doesn't prove
how much I love you. nothing will.

1527
01:46:20.541 --> 01:46:24.068
Every month is November. Sara.

1528
01:46:25.813 --> 01:46:27.804
And I love you every day.

1529
01:46:30.518 --> 01:46:31.917
Nelson. there's--

1530
01:46:32.120 --> 01:46:35.817
This is our month.
and it never has to end.

1531
01:46:44.831 --> 01:46:48.892
I surrender all attempts
to control life...

1532
01:46:49.202 --> 01:46:50.669
...yours or mine.

1533
01:46:51.938 --> 01:46:53.632
I live for one thing:

1534
01:46:54.773 --> 01:46:56.070
To love you.

1535
01:46:57.009 --> 01:46:58.636
To make you happy.

1536
01:46:59.578 --> 01:47:03.674
To live firmly and joyously
in the moment.

1537
01:47:04.683 --> 01:47:06.674
November is all I know.

1538
01:47:07.820 --> 01:47:09.787
And all I ever want to know.

1539
01:48:36.202 --> 01:48:37.601
What are you doing?

1540
01:48:38.938 --> 01:48:40.030
Where are you going?

1541
01:48:42.141 --> 01:48:43.130
Out.

1542
01:48:46.546 --> 01:48:49.344
This will give you time
to get your stuff together.

1543
01:48:50.983 --> 01:48:51.972
So you can go.

1544
01:48:52.918 --> 01:48:55.318
Our month is over.

1545
01:48:55.520 --> 01:48:56.953
Sara. I'm not leaving.

1546
01:48:59.825 --> 01:49:00.757
Sara!

1547
01:49:30.987 --> 01:49:32.545
Sara. stop!

1548
01:49:43.632 --> 01:49:46.294
Sara. stop running.
Sara!

1549
01:49:47.136 --> 01:49:48.626
Sara. please.

1550
01:49:49.905 --> 01:49:51.372
I'm not leaving you.

1551
01:49:51.573 --> 01:49:54.542
- I know you love me.
- I do.

1552
01:49:54.743 --> 01:49:56.176
I've never felt this.

1553
01:49:56.377 --> 01:49:59.710
I never thought I'd have the chance.
and you gave that to me. Nelson.

1554
01:49:59.914 --> 01:50:03.475
- Then why are you doing this?
- Because it's starting to happen.

1555
01:50:03.685 --> 01:50:04.845
I don't care.

1556
01:50:05.053 --> 01:50:08.352
Nelson. if you leave now. everything
we had will be perfect forever.

1557
01:50:08.556 --> 01:50:11.081
Sara. life isn't perfect.

1558
01:50:13.627 --> 01:50:16.960
All we have is how you'll remember me.

1559
01:50:17.464 --> 01:50:20.956
And I need that memory
to be strong and beautiful.

1560
01:50:23.470 --> 01:50:24.835
Don't you see?

1561
01:50:26.106 --> 01:50:30.769
If I know that I'm remembered
that way. then I can face anything.

1562
01:50:30.976 --> 01:50:32.068
Anything.

1563
01:50:33.579 --> 01:50:37.310
Nelson. you're my immortality.

1564
01:50:37.516 --> 01:50:39.313
I want to take care of you.

1565
01:50:39.752 --> 01:50:41.982
I'm gonna be all right.

1566
01:50:42.621 --> 01:50:44.282
I'm going home.

1567
01:50:45.958 --> 01:50:47.652
They know I'm coming.

1568
01:50:48.093 --> 01:50:50.584
I need to do this.

1569
01:50:51.696 --> 01:50:52.822
It doesn't seem--

1570
01:50:53.031 --> 01:50:57.161
Just like I need to know that you'll
go on and have a beautiful life.

1571
01:50:57.369 --> 01:50:58.802
The one you deserve.

1572
01:50:59.971 --> 01:51:01.495
I only want you.

1573
01:51:03.507 --> 01:51:04.974
You have me...

1574
01:51:05.943 --> 01:51:07.137
...forever.

1575
01:51:09.580 --> 01:51:11.480
Now let me go.

1576
01:51:20.356 --> 01:51:21.687
All right. Sara.

1577
01:51:24.127 --> 01:51:25.116
All right.

1578
01:51:27.497 --> 01:51:29.089
Close your eyes.

1579
01:51:52.220 --> 01:51:54.653
I love you. Nelson Moss.

1580
01:51:59.527 --> 01:52:01.757
I love you. Sara Deever.

1581
01:52:18.077 --> 01:52:19.442
Remember me.

